g.text: This workflow aims to study the correlation between income inequality
measured by the gini coefficient within different countries and some
variables chosen by our team that can be important factors regarding
income inequality. These factors we selected are the unemployment rate,
GDP per capita, population, poverty headcount ratio, tertiary education
For this we imported data of the explanatory variables for each European
country from Eurostat using SQL, and used Eurostat API to get the
country codes. We dowloaded the income inequality data from Kaggle,
created its schema in sql and read it into Knime. Furthermore we also
used the API of World Bank to get further explanatory variables.
Read files and write them into Term2's raw_data folder
Use API to get unemployment rate and gdppc from WDI
Analysis - correlation matrix and linear regressions
